<br>
Cueene<br>
36th Circle<br>
Psychic Venom<br>
Erollisi Marr <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=cueene>Cueene</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/15/01 12:17:35 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Where to solo 36+</span><hr size=1> There is about 6 spectres whenever I pull full spawn.<br>
<br>
Cueene<br>
36th Circle<br>
Psychic Venom<br>
Erollisi Marr <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/udrombacgunn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Drombac Gunn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/15/01 9:05:35 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> suggestion</span><hr size=1> try hill giants in rathe...good xp, GREAT money<br>
<br>
you wont be quad kiting them, but at that level..quad kiting is stil a bit too dangerous to be well worth it. as you found out, not only do you need skill and and the right spells..you need the right mob. if spectres were any good for quading at all...there would druids doin it 24/7... the best time fo quad kiting is 51+ with pillar spells..fast casting low cost 4 mob spells..seemingly designed for it.<br>
<br>
but if you simply must do it....head over to Kunark or velious and try experimenting there...you should find plenty of wide open space in either place, few poeple and lots of mobs to kite<br>
<br>
the poeple factor is a big one here, for while you inocently enough zoned to avoid being eaten by nasty spectres. more than likely more than one noob fell victim to its clutches as it lost you and went rampaging across the zone in rage. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwandork.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wandor K</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/16/01 12:12:48 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Where to solo 36+</span><hr size=1> at your level you should head for Eastern Wastes. You can probably quad walrus, if not, you can take walrus and ulthork hunters solo. By 39 you should easily be quading hunters and then switching to warriors around 40-41. It starts to green out at 43, but if the zone is empty you can still quad blues here. There are also a ton of frost giants in the area you can kite for loot and exp. <p><span style="font-size: 18px; font-famliy: arial"><b>Wandor Kilbringer<br>Wizard of the 43rd Conclave<br>Vini, Vidi, Nuki</b></span><br>
<i>I came, I saw, I nuked the crap out of everything in sight!</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utralantuebor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tralan Tuebor</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ancientfellowship.org/images/AF.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/25/01 5:46:26 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.ancientfellowship.org/images/tralan53.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Where to solo 36+</span><hr size=1> I have had some luck with the Drakkel Dire Wolves in GD.  Bonds of Force sticks to them fairly well, and as long as each one has been Temp Fluxed, they take full damage (205 @ 35).  Normally I'll take 3, just in case I get resists and need the mana to take out a stray.<br>
<br>
The wolves are slow and they help build Dwarf and Dragon Faction.  You only have to be careful of the giants.  They are fast, hit hard, and have way too many HP to solo effectively.  On ONE Frost Giant Scout (white to me @ 35) I burned all of my mana, used Harvest, AND had Clarity to put him down alone.<br>
<br>
IMO, giants just aren't worth soloing if they are even or higher con.  Stick with wolves in GD.<br>
<br>
<br>
Brindar<br>
Level 35 Wizard<br>
 <p><font face="Arial" size="2"><b><i>Tralan Tuebor</i></b></font><br>
<font face="Verdana" size="1">Ranger, 53rd Season<br>
Officer, <a href="http://www.ancientfellowship.org" target="_blank">Ancient Fellowship</a><br>
<a href="mailto:tralan@ancientfellowship.org">tralan@ancientfellowship.org</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=chiriko>chiriko</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/25/01 12:32:01 pm)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Where to solo 36+</span><hr size=1> Giants are a huge pain. at 36 It takes me a full bar of mana and harvest to take one of those bastards down, even when they're blue.. inferno shock just isn't efficient enough I guess.  Giants will probably become alot more doable at 39 when our big nuke isn't ice based.<br>
<br>
-Chiriko, lvl 36 wizard, Innoruuk <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ucryndarkfire.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cryn Darkfire</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC= http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif  BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/7/01 9:48:21 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Where to solo 36+</span><hr size=1> Its not quad kiting but dorfs in BB are doable at this level.<br>
<br>
Hmmm<br>
<br>
Any other suggestions guys? I'm looking for the same thing!<br>
<br>
Cryn<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utotenkopftz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TotenkopfTZ</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://freepages.ugo.com/totenkopftz/files/totenk.jpg Width=20 Height=20 BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/7/01 10:16:28 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://freepages.ugo.com/Totenkopftz/files/Toten1.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Where to solo 36+</span><hr size=1> Hate to break this to you but Velious Giants are VERY tough to solo even at 41st level. If you can kill one you will be nearly OOM when you're done.<br>
<br>
I have been told that at 44th level when we get conflag you can do giants solo and they're still blue.<br>
<br>
I did 36th through 40th primarily in Crystal Caverns. Orcs are blue through 39th and the dungeon experience there is terrific. If the dungeon is too crowded you can kill single walruses outside in the SW part of EW.<br>
<br>
Currently I'm quad-kiting drakkel dire wolves in GD. I get nearly a full blue bubble per pull of four (though I prefer three) and they rarely resist bonds. Plus I'm getting Coldain faction and some minimal dragon faction to boot. <p><center><br><font size = 4><font color=yellow><b>"Aces high, Baby...and you just drew the death card."</font></font></b><br><EMBED src="http://freepages.ugo.com/totenkopftz/files/Toten9.swf" quality=high loop=true WIDTH=400 HEIGHT=100 TYPE="application/x-shockwave-flash" PLUGINSPAGE="http://www.macromedia.com/shockwave/download/index.cgi?P1_Prod_Version=ShockwaveFlash"> </EMBED>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uspankda.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Spankda</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/8/01 5:32:33 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Where to solo 36+</span><hr size=1> The Overthere is full of blues and reds to my 33 Wiz.  Easy to pull a single and if all goes bad, you can zone.  Better if you're not KOS to the Dragoons. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showMessage?topicID=75.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showMessage?topicID=91.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.emailToFriend?topicID=64.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.threadControl?topicID=64.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=64.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=64.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub23.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method